# arvo-tensor — backlog

> **Type-surface reminder**: new entries use `arvo::USize` /
> `Bool` / `UFixed<N, 0, S>` instead of `usize` / `bool` / `u*`;
> `notko::Maybe` / `Outcome` instead of `Option` / `Result`. See
> `rules/type-surface.md`.

## Higher-rank shapes

Future rank-N containers as consumer demand surfaces:

- Grid<T, const N: Cap, const M: Cap> — rectangular 2D (non-square Matrix).
  Needed when an algorithm has N rows × M columns with N != M.
- Cube<T, const N: Cap, const M: Cap, const P: Cap> — rank-3. Needed for
  3D spectral workloads or ML-adjacent tensor ops.

Each shape follows the same pattern: `#[repr(transparent)]` wrapper over
the raw fixed-size array-of-arrays, `get` / `set` methods taking USize
indices, `from_fn` constructor, IntoIterator impl, participates in the
Enumerator trait.

## core::ops / Index impls

Adding `impl Index<USize> for Array<T, N>` and `impl Index<(USize, USize)>
for Matrix<W, N>` enables `arr[idx]` / `matrix[(i, j)]` syntax. Deferred
from the initial round to keep scope focused; get/set methods suffice for
day-one migration.

## ArrayLen trait (generalised cap_size)

`cap_size(c: Cap) -> usize` is a single-purpose bridge. A trait family
like `pub trait ArrayLen { const LEN: usize; }` implemented on cap-like
types could generalise the pattern — every newtype wrapping a usize that
wants to participate in array sizing implements ArrayLen. #121 covers the
underlying language blocker; ArrayLen is a possible trait-level framing
once that resolves.

## Tensor trait surface

If a second rank-specific container surfaces (e.g. Grid) that shares
structure with Array + Matrix, promote common methods to a `Tensor`
trait. Candidate methods: `len() -> USize` (total cell count), `fill(v)`,
`map<U, F>(f: F) -> Self::Mapped<U>`. Only do when the third concrete
container materialises; premature abstraction otherwise.

## Consumer migration

Each downstream sweep round (arvo-graph, arvo-sparse, arvo-spectral)
drops its raw `&[T; cap_size(N)]` signatures in favour of
`&Array<T, N>`. Internal DP tables become `Matrix<W, N>`. Bit-shaped
adjacency stays on arvo-bitmask. Tracked per-crate under the #120
umbrella.

## Internal source sweep for bare primitives

Per workspace rule `.claude/rules/no-bare-primitives.md` and round
202604500000, replace bare `u8` / `u16` / `u32` / `u64` / `i*` / `usize`
in non-exception positions with arvo aliases (`Uint8` / `Uint16` /
`Uint32` / `Uint64` / `Int*` / `USize`). Exception positions
(definition-site bottom-outs) stay bare; everything else migrates.
Tracked as a follow-up sweep once the upstream arvo / arvo-bits /
arvo-hash migrations land.
